# Group Events

Represents event information.

---

**Event Attributes:**
- id `(String)` : Event's unique ID, **Required**
- version `(Number)` : Event's version number
- lastEditedAt `(Integer)` : Last time this event was edited, as a unix timestamp
- lastEditedBy `(String)` : Last person to edit this event
- createdAt `(Integer)` : Time this event was created, as a unix timestamp
- createdBy `(String)` : Person that created this event
- institutionId `(String)` : This is used when institutions have a seperate unique identifier for each

- name `(String)` : Event's name, **Required**
- type `(String)` : Type of the event. Different event types have different event forms, and the calendar can show different event types in different colors, **Required**
- description `(String)` : Event's description, This description will show up in the public events page, **Required**
- organization `(String)` :  ID of organization who is hosting the event, **Required**, ***Oranization Reference***
- authorId `(String)` : ID of the user who created the event, ***User Reference***
- authorType `(String)` : The type of event author
- owners `(Array<String>)` : ID of all users set as owners of this event, ***User Reference***
- contacts `(Array<Contact Object>)` : List of event's contacts
- cost `(String | Float)` : Event's cost
- discount `(Float)` : Event's cost discount
- administrativeFeePercentage `(Integer)` : Event's cost administrative fee percentage, out of 100
- administrativeFeeValue `(Float)` : Event's cost administrative fee value
- contractId `(String)` : Event's associated contract
- imageURL `(String)` : URL of the image that will be shown alongside the event content in the public event page
- attachments `(Array<Attachment Object>)` : List of URL links for any additional file attachments, **Required**
- notes `(String)` : Event notes. This field will not be shown on the public event page. It is for internal use only

- expectedHeadCount `(Number)` : Predicted Head Count of the event
- registeredHeadCount `(Number)` : Number of registered event attendees
- actualHeadCount `(Number)` : Number of event attendees

- status `(String)` : Status of the event. Default is ‘Confirmed’. New events that have not been approved have status = “Pending”
- featured `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a featured event. Featured events get shown on home page of Public Event Site
- private `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a private event. Private events will not show up in public event site, but will show up in Event Dashboard. However, all event details will be redacted for all users except the event author
- hidden `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a hidden event. Hidden events will not show up in public event site. Additionally, the event will not show up in the event dashboard for any user except the author of the event

- sectionInfo `(Array<Section Info Object>)` : List of event's related sections

- meetings `(Array<Meeting Object>)` : List of event's meetings

- customFields (Object) : This event's custom field values

The following are GET-only APIs; no PUT, POST, or DELETE will be supported.

- eventPriceOverride `(Float)`:  (Invoiced Event Price) The edited total event price displayed on an Event invoice

- stripeInvoiceLink `(String)`: If the Stripe integration toggle is ON for an event, the invoice link generated in Stripe for an Event

- description `(String)` :  (Payment Instructions) Notes on payment that can be added to the invoice

- roomTotal `(Float)`: Total price charged for a Room within one Event

- invoicedRoomTotal `(Float)` :  (Invoiced Room Price) The edited total Room price displayed on an Event invoice

- resource `(Array<Required Resource Object>)` :  List of Event's resources

- resourceTotal `(Float)`: Total price charged for an individual Resource within one Event

- invoicedResourceTotal `(Float)` :  The edited total Resource price displayed on an Event invoice

**Attachment Object:**
- url `(String)` : Attachment's URL, **Required**
- name `(String)` : Attachment's name, **Required**

**Meeting Attributes:**
- id `(String)` : Meeting's unique ID, **Required**
- eventId `(String)` : Meeting's event's unique ID, ***Event Reference***

- roomId `(String)` : Meeting's room's ID, **Required**, ***Room Reference***
- layout `(String)` : Meeting's layout
- resources `(Array<Required Resource Object>)` : List of meeting's resources, **Required**

- startDate `(String)` : Meeting's start date in 'YYYY-MM-DD' format, **Required**
- endDate `(String)` : Meeting's end date in 'YYYY-MM-DD' format, **Required**
- startTime `(Number)` : Meeting's start time, **Required**
- endTime `(Number)` : Meeting's end time, **Required**
- allDay `(Boolean)` : Whether object is all day 
- patternId `(String)` : Meeting's repeat pattern id
- pattern `(Pattern Object)` : Meeting's repeat pattern
- patternChild `(Boolean)` : Whether this meeting is a pattern child
- patternParent `(Boolean)` : Whether this meeting is a pattern parent

- status `(String)` : Meeting's status
- featured `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a featured event. Featured events get shown on home page of Public Event Site
- private `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a private event. Private events will not show up in public event site, but will show up in Event Dashboard. However, all event details will be redacted for all users except the event author
- hidden `(Boolean)` : Flag indicating a hidden event. Hidden events will not show up in public event site. Additionally, the event will not show up in the event dashboard for any user except the author of the event

- parentMeeting `(String)` : Meeting's info about parent meetings
- moveWithParent `(Boolean)` : Whether meeting should move with parent
- isSetup `(Boolean)` : Whether meeting is for setup 
- isTeardown `(Boolean)` : Whether meeting is for teardown 

- sectionInfo `(Array<Section Info Object>)` : List of meeting's related sections

**Required Resource Object:**
- id `(String)` : Resource's ID, **Required**, ***Resource Reference***
- quanitity `(Number)` : Needed quantity of referenced resource, **Required**

**Pattern Object:**
- unit `(String)` : Pattern's unit of stepping, **Required**
- step `(Number)` : Pattern's number of steps, **Required**
- days `(Array<Number>)` : Pattern's days, **Required**
- dateLimit `(String)` : Pattern's last date
- numberLimit `(Number)` : Pattern's last step number
- label `(String)` : A label for this pattern

**Section Info Object:**
- year `(String)` : Section's year, **Required**
- semester `(String)` : Section's semester, **Required**
- sectionId `(String)` : Section's ID, **Required**, ***Section Reference***
- courseId `(String)` : Section's course's ID, **Required**, ***Course Reference***

